DO YOU KNOW how to break in a freshly build engine?!
Let me know if you do the same ?! 

Ray who build engine for the best in business share this with me as a startup process 👍
.
10/40wt motorcycle engine oil non synthetic I like to use Maxima ATV 10/40wt for break in
Then Maxima Extra 10/40wt after first oil change 
Change oil after break-in
Coolant Engine ice or Evans 
VP C12 fuel
Make sure you charge your battery 
Clean air filter

Upon initial start up of a fresh engine, make sure that the engine is getting oil to the top end. You can simply do this by checking the dip stick if it went down oil is cycling. Good time to check for leaks and add coolant and oil if needed. 
3-Idle periods, 3-Cool down periods with fan blowing on radiator. 
Step 1.
Start engine and let idle with a fan blowing on the front of the engine, to get air to the radiator. Let engine idle for 10 minutes. Check for leaks. 
Step 2.
Shut engine off after 10 minutes of running and let machine cool down for 30 minutes. Let fan continue to blow on engine.
Repeat first step
Repeat second step.
Repeat first step.
Repeat second step.

First ride: Ride machine for 10 minutes. Make sure to vary your RPM range. Ride machine at 50% of your normal riding pace. Be careful not to lug or over rev the motor during break-in.
COOL DOWN: After 10 minutes of riding, shut machine off and let machine cool down for a minimum of 30 minutes.
RIDE: Repeat initial riding period. But ride for 10 minutes at 60% of your normal pace. 
COOL DOWN: Shut machine off and let machine cool down for a minimum of 30min. 
One tank full is full break in period. 

Let me know if you have any questions. 
.
